orption costing system and sells three types of products. The company faces challenges in maintaining revenues and profits due to economic recession. Sales prices fluctuate, and a market specialist sets budgeted sales prices each quarter. The sales manager negotiates actual sales prices with customers.\"", "\"STANDARD SELLING PRICE\":\"Standard selling price is the budgeted price set for a product at the beginning of a period, based on market expectations.\"", "\"VARIABLE PRODUCTION COSTS\":\"Variable production costs are costs that vary directly with the level of production, such as materials and labor.\"", "\"COMMODITY 2\":\"Commodity 2 refers to a specific product with actual production and sales units of 30,400, an actual selling price per unit of $34, and an average market price per unit of $33.15.\"", "\"COMMODITY 3\":\"Commodity 3 refers to a specific product with actual production and sales units of 25,600, an actual selling price per unit of $40.40, and an average market price per unit of $39.10.\"", "\"SALES PRICE OPERATIONAL VARIANCE\":\"Sales price operational variance is calculated as (actual price - market price) * actual quantity.\"", "\"SALES PRICE PLANNING VARIANCE\":\"Sales price planning variance is calculated as (standard price - market price) * actual quantity.\"", "\"TOTAL SALES MIX VARIANCE\":\"Total sales mix variance is calculated by comparing the actual quantity in the actual mix to the actual quantity in the standard mix, multiplied by the standard profit.\"", "\"TOTAL SALES QUANTITY VARIANCE\":\"Total sales quantity variance is calculated by comparing the actual quantity in the standard mix to the budgeted sales, multiplied by the standard profit.\"", "\"PERFORMANCE OF THE BUSINESS AND SALES MANAGER\":\"The performance of the business and the sales manager for the quarter ended 31 May can be evaluated by analyzing the calculated variances for sales price operational, sales price planning, total sales mix, and total sales quantity.\"", "\"